    	 <p>Start planning your Amazing Grace event today. All you need are a singer (or 100!), and if you have one, a recording device to capture the moment. (Wondering how to get a video? <a href="/amazinggrace/faq.htm#2">Click here</a>.)</p>
    	  <p>Here are some questions to get the creative juices flowing:</p>
    	  <ul>
    	    <li>What musical resources do we have in our parish (vocal, instrumental, rhythmic)?<br />
    	      <br />
    	    </li>
    	    <li>Is there an interesting location inside or outside our church where we could film this?<br />
    	      <br />
    	    </li>
    	    <li>How can we draw on skills from people of different ages?<br />
    	      <br />
    	    </li>
    	    <li>Is there a unique cultural angle we could take on the hymn? (What about “Amazing Grace” in Cantonese? Or sung to a reggae beat?)</li>
          </ul>
